metadata.name: Truchet Towers #81
metadata.description:
Curved Truchet tiling is laid down on a 3D plane forming an imaginary landscape of ripples.

The longest continuous line created by the tiling is removed, cutting a path through the terrain.
This occurs within 3D space and may or may not appear within the confines of the canvas frame,
but most likely will appear.

A tower rises up to wherever a circle is created by the tiling. Driven by the random
tiling, zero or several of these may appear within the frame. Shadows differ in each mint.

In addition to working on decorative tiling, Sébastien Truchet worked on canals and sundials,
forming the inspiration for the exploration of shade and shadow in this work.

Mints will have a variety of earth-tone background colors with each perspective of the scene
slightly different to produce diverse results.

As I researched Sébastien Truchet I learned that he worked with hydraulics and canal design,
as well as sundials. This became the inspiration for my new shading and shadowing technique used
in this piece.

For me this piece evokes a sense of agriculture, and connects me to an imaginary
landscape that could have looked familiar to Truchet in 18th century France.

This work was created with my own javascript, utilizing my polyline path helper library I
maintain at https://github.com/markroland/path-helper.

metadata.name: WEIRD FISHES 4, 5 and 6 #26
metadata.description:
Weird Fish 4 - The Golden Waterpig (45% probability)
Weird Fish 5 - The Killer Angler (35% probability)
Weird Fish 6 - The Lumpy Seahorse (20% probability)

These are the 4th, 5th and 6th in a collection of 10 fish
Each next drop will have less possible iterations making the new fish more rare



This token features:
Many different coral reefs in various colours
Fishes in different sizes and colours
Small fish banks in random number and colour
Random bubbles
Random speed
Perline noise plancton in different quantities size and colour

metadata.name: The beautiful mistake #22
metadata.description:
That work is just a programming mistake, but it has grown into generative art.
I worked with a different types of noise with the library fastNoise for js.
Here you can see different combinations of noises in each cell, which intertwined between each other that gives you abstract picture. There is animation of generating.
- You can save art in that resolution on "S" in PNG

metadata.name: Divers N1 #12
metadata.description:
I remember holding my breath and sitting on the bottom of the public pool where I spent most summers. Every so often I would hear a sound like breaking glass played by a transistor radio  and turn see the form of a diver plunging into the deep end. 

Consider the form of a diver seconds after they hit water. I am struck the grace of a freefall, the shock of transition from air to water, and the shedding of bits the old world carried with the skin. 

Formally this piece is also my attempt to blend a kind of lyrical figurativism with the technical and aesthetic demands of long-form token based generative art. In this piece, a randomized subset of digitally sculpted  forms are loaded, spatially transformed via heuristics and RNG, and then translated into simple animated particle systems. 

This process of transformation occurs a variable number of times, so each piece could contain the base form of anywhere between 1 and 10 divers.

this piece was created with threejs

metadata.name: Layered Landscapes #7
metadata.description:
Layered Landscapes explores representing imaginary landscapes through line art designed for output with a pen plotter.

It supports these variations:

Hill Contours: 4 layers
Dark Foreground: 50% chance the first contour is overprinted for darker darks
Sky: straight or curved
fog: 0, 1 or 2 layers
trees: 1 to 7

Press "s" to download the SVG.

Output is designed for 6" x 4".

metadata.name: Fax Abstraction #23
metadata.description:
The work was created from neurally generated with Latent Diffusion pictorial abstractions, which I was inspired by the work of Gerhard Richter.
They were further hybridized in the spirit of pointillism and Yayoi Kusama and the vintage fax art aesthetic.
Therefore, this work is about the friendship of different artistic styles coexisting together : )

Thanks Yulikolay for help in its creation!
